    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Registers that record the administration of the sacrament of baptism to members of a community. In historical usage, these registers also served as important civic documents, in that they recorded the approximate date of birth and names of new babies, their parents, and baptismal sponsors in the community.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
